## Conclusion

The evidence overwhelmingly supports the need for more women in leadership roles. Women leaders contribute significantly to improved financial performance, innovation, and organizational culture. Their unique leadership styles and values complement existing management approaches, fostering more inclusive and effective workplaces. Beyond corporate benefits, increasing women’s leadership advances broader economic growth and social equity.

To realize these benefits, organizations and societies must actively dismantle barriers to women’s leadership through supportive policies, mentorship programs, and cultural change initiatives. This is not merely a matter of fairness but a strategic imperative to enhance competitiveness and sustainability in the global economy.

